content:
Give your customers the information and support they need with Service Cloud—the customer service application that you can customize to fit your needs.

With Service Cloud, you can choose how your customers reach you—by email, phone, messaging apps, Experience Cloud sites, chat, text, and more. To keep your customers satisfied when they do contact you, Service Cloud makes sure that your agents have all the tools they need to respond efficiently to customer questions and requests.

You can track and anticipate customer issues, boost agent productivity, and honor service-level agreements with key Service Cloud tools. Use Service Cloud's productivity tools to help agents work efficiently in the Service Console.

Help your customers help themselves by building and publishing a comprehensive knowledge base. Automatically turn requests for your company’s products and services into orders with Service Catalog.

Service Cloud offers many ways for your customers to contact you: phone, web chat, WhatsApp, and more. Set up a mix of support channels to help customers in a familiar setting.

Unify your channels and manage your agent workload with Omni-Channel routing. Set up rules and queues to automate your service process.

Einstein for Service is a powerful set of time-saving AI features that support your agents in providing excellent service experiences. Track service metrics and manage your team by accessing or creating reports and visualizations that help you track service activity and KPIs in real time, with a little help from AI.

Engage customers and users with relevant, personalized surveys using Salesforce Feedback Management. Incorporate survey data into your feedback management process to gain actionable insights throughout the customer lifecycle.

Learn about Salesforce Field Service and Click Field Service Edge. Honor the privacy and preferences of your customers and service agents by taking a human-centric approach to customer service.

You can also locate documentation for earlier versions of Service features we've upgraded, and use guides to help you learn about and successfully administer your Service Cloud features.
title: Service Cloud: Customer Support and Service Application
